identifying the stuff that's

00:27:00.730 --> 00:27:04.230
there that isn't adding
information to our visuals

00:27:04.230 --> 00:27:07.330
and stripping those
unnecessary elements away.

00:27:07.330 --> 00:27:09.450
Fourth chapter is on
focusing attention.

00:27:09.450 --> 00:27:13.110
What we looked at today is just
a small subset of much broader

00:27:13.110 --> 00:27:15.620
content that's covered there.

00:27:15.620 --> 00:27:17.840
Fifth lesson is on
thinking like a designer.

00:27:17.840 --> 00:27:19.680
I talk about how
you can leverage

00:27:19.680 --> 00:27:23.430
some concepts of traditional
design, things like affordances

00:27:23.430 --> 00:27:26.880
and accessibility and building
acceptance with your audience

00:27:26.880 --> 00:27:29.480
when it comes to
visualizing data.

00:27:29.480 --> 00:27:33.520
Chapter six looks at a number of
what I consider model visuals,

00:27:33.520 --> 00:27:35.560
and I talk about
the design thought

00:27:35.560 --> 00:27:38.230
process used to create those.

00:27:38.230 --> 00:27:40.824
Chapter 7 is focused on story.

00:27:40.824 --> 00:27:42.240
And again, what
we looked at today

00:27:42.240 --> 00:27:44.710
is just a small piece of that.

00:27:44.710 --> 00:27:46.780
Chapter 8 pulls all of
these lessons together.

00:27:46.780 --> 00:27:50.040
It goes through a single
example from start to finish,

00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:52.700
showing all of these
in coordination.

00:27:52.700 --> 00:27:55.500
Chapter 9 covers
a number of case

00:27:55.500 --> 00:27:58.800
studies on common challenges
faced when visualizing data.

00:27:58.800 --> 00:28:01.600
And then the final
chapter is a wrap-up,

00:28:01.600 --> 00:28:03.920
a recap of what's
learned, talk about where

00:28:03.920 --> 00:28:07.020
to go next, and discuss
building storytelling with data

00:28:07.020 --> 00:28:11.300
competency in your team
and in your organization.

