want to stay away
from some of the stuff

00:33:41.940 --> 00:33:43.336
that we talked about here today.

00:33:43.336 --> 00:33:45.210
Because as soon as you
use color, especially,

00:33:45.210 --> 00:33:47.168
to draw your audience's
attention to one story,

00:33:47.168 --> 00:33:50.390
it actually makes any other
potential stories much harder

00:33:50.390 --> 00:33:51.650
to see.

00:33:51.650 --> 00:33:55.530
So dashboards, you want to think
about designing in grays when

00:33:55.530 --> 00:33:59.720
you can or using color only as
a categorical differentiator,

00:33:59.720 --> 00:34:04.360
not as a visual cue that
says, draw attention here.

00:34:04.360 --> 00:34:07.410
Dashboards for me fit-- I
talked about this distinction

00:34:07.410 --> 00:34:10.010
between exploratory
and explanatory.

00:34:10.010 --> 00:34:12.560
And for me, dashboards fit
more in the exploratory

00:34:12.560 --> 00:34:15.000
but I think often get
sort of tried to be

00:34:15.000 --> 00:34:16.360
used for the explanatory.

00:34:16.360 --> 00:34:19.388
Where a dashboard is sort of,
I've got all of these metrics

00:34:19.388 --> 00:34:20.929
on a single page,
on a single screen.

00:34:20.929 --> 00:34:21.679
I can scan through them.

00:34:21.679 --> 00:34:23.030
I can look for where
things are in line

00:34:23.030 --> 00:34:24.946
with what I expect, where
are they not in line

00:34:24.946 --> 00:34:27.339
with what I expect,
and then pick out, hey,

00:34:27.339 --> 00:34:28.880
something might be
interesting there.

00:34:28.880 --> 00:34:30.420
And then dig in on that.

00:34:30.420 --> 00:34:32.829
And when you can find the
interesting thing, then instead

00:34:32.829 --> 00:34:34.620
of using the dashboard
to communicate that,

00:34:34.620 --> 00:34:37.000
my view is that you should do
the stuff we talked about today

00:34:37.000 --> 00:34:38.666
and take that interesting
thing and make

00:34:38.666 --> 00:34:41.050
that the focus and
not necessarily

00:34:41.050 --> 00:34:43.260
confine yourself to
the dashboard for that.

00:34:43.260 --> 00:34:45.340
Because the challenge
in trying to communicate

00:34:45.340 --> 00:34:48.429
to an audience with a dashboard
is by showing them so much,

00:34:48.429 --> 00:34:51.574
it's hard to draw attention
to one particular place.

