00:47:18.930 --> 00:47:21.120
how do you make that
work for your audience?

00:47:21.120 --> 00:47:23.010
And now data is different
because it's not

00:47:23.010 --> 00:47:24.860
sort of a tangible thing.

00:47:24.860 --> 00:47:27.610
So the things you
have at your disposal

00:47:27.610 --> 00:47:31.640
to show how to use
something is not tangible.

00:47:31.640 --> 00:47:33.320
It's visual.

00:47:33.320 --> 00:47:35.880
So then it's thinking about,
how do you visualize this?

00:47:35.880 --> 00:47:39.420
How do people see, bringing in
some of those sorts of things.

00:47:39.420 --> 00:47:43.140
One example that I like-- are
people familiar with the OXO

00:47:43.140 --> 00:47:45.610
brand of kitchen gadgets?

00:47:45.610 --> 00:47:48.470
So there's things like
vegetable peelers or spatulas

00:47:48.470 --> 00:47:50.990
or like a garlic press.

00:47:50.990 --> 00:47:55.010
And if you just sort of
lay them out on a counter,

00:47:55.010 --> 00:47:56.691
it's intuitive how
to pick them up.

00:47:56.691 --> 00:47:59.190
And you don't even realize that
when you're picking them up,

00:47:59.190 --> 00:48:01.030
because they're
formed in a way that's

00:48:01.030 --> 00:48:02.738
going to make you pick
them up in the way

00:48:02.738 --> 00:48:04.450
they're intended
to be used, which

00:48:04.450 --> 00:48:06.326
is brilliant from a
design standpoint.

00:48:06.326 --> 00:48:07.700
And we want to
think about how we

00:48:07.700 --> 00:48:12.470
can leverage those same sort of
cues when it comes to our data.

00:48:12.470 --> 00:48:14.640
How do you make it so
obvious to the audience

00:48:14.640 --> 00:48:17.140
how they're supposed to use
that data that they can't use

00:48:17.140 --> 00:48:19.700
it any other way, that
they can't help but see

00:48:19.700 --> 00:48:21.860
what you want them to see?

00:48:21.860 --> 00:48:24.430
So design is probably
one of the big places

00:48:24.430 --> 00:48:26.470
that I drew from when
it came to researching

00:48:26.470 --> 00:48:28.029
some of the stuff for the book.

